item.title: [ENTESB-4472] [Patch mechanism] Upgrading SSH container results into wrong merged system.properties and general problem with reconnecting to fabric
item.description:
Issue is related to ENTESB-4431 . Steps are for reproduction are the same. The difference is that now the container is started using container-start but it never reconnects to fabric (the karaf process is running on remote machine). Also it is important to note that executing bin/client on remote doesn't connect to it.

Roman Jakubco, Jason Sherman, Jonathan Anstey, Hiram Chirino, Fintan Bolton, Emil Cervenan, Matej Melko:
So the fragment that should go to the documentation should be more or less like this:

IMPORTANT: ssh containers are created from fabric8-karaf-1.2.0.redhat-133.zip distribution, but the problem is that distro may be:

  • zipped on the fly from what's currently available in FUSE_HOME of root container
  • official (from Maven) fabric8-karaf-1.2.0.redhat-133.zip

Patch management checks whether etc/startup.properties file in those distro contain (then it's "baseline-ssh-fuse"), or not (then it's "baseline-ssh-fabric8") this line:

org/jboss/fuse/shared-commands/6.2.0.redhat-133/shared-commands-6.2.0.redhat-133.jar=50

So, in order to have no problem described in this issue, customer/user has to make sure, that FUSE_HOME/system/io/fabric8/fabric8-karaf/1.2.0.redhat-133 directory contains two artifacts:

  • fabric8-karaf-1.2.0.redhat-133-custom.zip
  • fabric8-karaf-1.2.0.redhat-133.zip

It doesn't really matter which is which - it's very important that these are different. User/Customer has to check the fabric8-karaf-1.2.0.redhat-133.zip files that should be placed "near" unzipped and running SSH containers. Then the distro should be compared to what's currently in FUSE_HOME/system/io/fabric8/fabric8-karaf/1.2.0.redhat-133 - this may or may not be the same distro. If they're the same, than SSH containers were actually created from what's in FUSE_HOME/system/io/fabric8/fabric8-karaf/1.2.0.redhat-133, but if they're not the same, one ZIP should be renamed to fabric8-karaf-1.2.0.redhat-133-custom.zip and placed in FUSE_HOME/system/io/fabric8/fabric8-karaf/1.2.0.redhat-133.

Only then patch management should be "initialized" according to documentation.
